From: twisti-dev <76837088+twisti-dev@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Thu, 9 Jul 2026 21:24:53 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] Add calling-plugin dispatcher accessors

Introduce Dispatchers.GlobalDispatcher, Dispatchers.forEntity,
Dispatchers.forRegion and Dispatchers.forPlugin extensions on the
kotlinx Dispatchers object. Unlike the existing Plugin.* accessors these
take no Plugin receiver: the owning plugin is resolved from the caller
class via MethodHandles and cached per class, so plugin code can obtain a
dispatcher without threading a Plugin reference through every call site.
They are inline and @JvmSynthetic on purpose, so the caller-class lookup
is correct and the API stays Kotlin-only (it cannot resolve a plugin from
Java call sites).

To support withContext(Dispatchers.forEntity(entity)) ergonomically, the
underlying Plugin.globalRegionDispatcher, mainDispatcher, entityDispatcher
and regionDispatcher accessors now return CoroutineDispatcher instead of
CoroutineContext. Binary-compatible @Deprecated(HIDDEN) overloads with the
former CoroutineContext return type are kept so already-compiled plugins
keep linking.

Also drops two stray IDE auto-imports (org.eclipse.sisu.Hidden and the
redundant kotlin.jvm.java) that were unused.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

